1
00:01:53,840 --> 00:01:55,079
Ms. Liu, slow down, Ms. Liu.

2
00:01:55,079 --> 00:01:55,799
Slow down, slow down.

3
00:01:55,840 --> 00:01:56,719
Slow down, Ms. Liu.

4
00:01:57,280 --> 00:01:57,840
What's wrong?

5
00:01:57,840 --> 00:01:58,599
Boss Li.

6
00:01:59,140 --> 00:01:59,959
Ms. Liu is here.

7
00:02:00,019 --> 00:02:00,640
Ms. Liu is here.

8
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:01,680
Where are you feeling unwell?

9
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:05,159
Where am I feeling unwell?

10
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:06,799
We're asking you.

11
00:02:07,620 --> 00:02:08,539
My whole body...

12
00:02:09,340 --> 00:02:10,219
Whole body...

13
00:02:11,259 --> 00:02:12,259
Whole body...

14
00:02:12,699 --> 00:02:13,819
My head hurts.

15
00:02:13,819 --> 00:02:14,960
You have heads all over your body?

16
00:02:15,180 --> 00:02:16,939
No, you mean a headache, right?

17
00:02:16,939 --> 00:02:18,340
Here, let me take a look.

18
00:02:18,379 --> 00:02:19,580
Do you have a fever?

19
00:02:19,580 --> 00:02:20,460
Let's check the temperature.

20
00:02:22,900 --> 00:02:24,139
That feels much better.

21
00:02:24,340 --> 00:02:25,539
That feels much better.

22
00:02:26,580 --> 00:02:28,099
Ms. Liu, you have magic hands.

23
00:02:28,099 --> 00:02:29,900
No, his temperature isn't high.

24
00:02:29,900 --> 00:02:30,500
It's just...

25
00:02:30,699 --> 00:02:32,219
Why is there so much cold sweat?

26
00:02:32,219 --> 00:02:33,419
Exactly.

27
00:02:34,780 --> 00:02:35,699
Perhaps...

28
00:02:36,300 --> 00:02:38,699
I was infected by Professor Fan.

29
00:02:39,699 --> 00:02:42,900
I've been taking care of the patient non-stop these days.

30
00:02:44,460 --> 00:02:46,080
Maybe it triggered my...

31
00:02:46,080 --> 00:02:47,659
old chronic insomnia...

32
00:02:47,659 --> 00:02:49,259
and flared it up.

33
00:02:53,060 --> 00:02:56,300
Illness really comes like a landslide.

34
00:02:58,219 --> 00:02:59,500
Ms. Liu.

35
00:03:00,340 --> 00:03:01,780
I'm sorry about this.

36
00:03:01,780 --> 00:03:02,699
It's okay.

37
00:03:02,860 --> 00:03:03,740
This time...

38
00:03:04,340 --> 00:03:06,500
I'm afraid I'll have to trouble you again.

39
00:03:06,659 --> 00:03:07,500
It's fine.

40
00:03:09,539 --> 00:03:11,819
You really treat Ms. Liu like a professional caregiver.

41
00:03:12,500 --> 00:03:14,659
She took care of me because...

42
00:03:15,060 --> 00:03:15,659
Right?

43
00:03:16,020 --> 00:03:16,740
As for you...

44
00:03:16,819 --> 00:03:17,780
I think we should call...

45
00:03:17,819 --> 00:03:19,580
Zhu Zhu and Yusheng to come take care of you.

46
00:03:20,060 --> 00:03:22,379
Or just have Dr. Chang send a male caregiver.

47
00:03:22,659 --> 00:03:23,259
Come back.

48
00:03:23,860 --> 00:03:25,539
Why is it that when you were sick,

49
00:03:25,659 --> 00:03:27,580
you had Ms. Liu to take care of you?

50
00:03:27,939 --> 00:03:28,979
But when I'm sick,

51
00:03:29,219 --> 00:03:30,900
I get a male caregiver?

52
00:03:31,460 --> 00:03:32,860
It's the same illness.

53
00:03:33,259 --> 00:03:35,860
I demand the same treatment.

54
00:03:35,860 --> 00:03:36,500
Old Li.

55
00:03:36,500 --> 00:03:38,900
It hasn't been confirmed it's the same illness yet.

56
00:03:39,539 --> 00:03:40,180
How about...

57
00:03:40,819 --> 00:03:42,500
I go get Royal Physician Sun to take a look.

58
00:03:42,500 --> 00:03:43,819
No.

59
00:03:44,979 --> 00:03:46,300
Such a minor illness...

60
00:03:46,740 --> 00:03:49,939
shouldn't disturb Royal Physician Sun.

61
00:03:50,620 --> 00:03:51,659
I think...

62
00:03:52,379 --> 00:03:54,900
Ms. Liu will do.

63
00:03:57,819 --> 00:03:58,740
Alright, then...

64
00:03:58,939 --> 00:04:00,500
Open your mouth.

65
00:04:01,099 --> 00:04:02,020
Ahh.

66
00:04:04,539 --> 00:04:06,340
I can't make sense of this either.

67
00:04:06,379 --> 00:04:08,180
We should get a professional. Let...

68
00:04:08,300 --> 00:04:09,259
Let Royal Physician Sun come...

69
00:04:09,259 --> 00:04:10,900
and prescribe you some medicine or something.

70
00:04:11,620 --> 00:04:13,979
I said no need, so no need.

71
00:04:14,900 --> 00:04:16,339
Just take Professor Fan's...

72
00:04:16,660 --> 00:04:18,139
leftover medicine...

73
00:04:18,139 --> 00:04:20,980
give me two pills to try, that'll be enough.

74
00:04:22,139 --> 00:04:25,579
It'd be a pity to throw the leftovers away.

75
00:04:26,220 --> 00:04:27,100
I think...

76
00:04:27,699 --> 00:04:29,660
I should just drink more water.

77
00:04:30,300 --> 00:04:31,800
Ms. Liu, could you...

78
00:04:31,939 --> 00:04:34,019
get me some hot water?

79
00:04:34,300 --> 00:04:35,379
You want hot water, right?

80
00:04:35,420 --> 00:04:35,980
I'll go pour it for you.

81
00:04:35,980 --> 00:04:37,339
No.

82
00:04:39,779 --> 00:04:40,860
Sister Cai.

83
00:04:41,620 --> 00:04:43,899
You just go about your business.

84
00:04:44,339 --> 00:04:47,220
You've been working hard these days too.

85
00:04:47,899 --> 00:04:50,540
Managing a myriad of affairs is very exhausting.

86
00:04:51,019 --> 00:04:53,779
We can't have you wearing yourself out.

87
00:04:53,860 --> 00:04:54,699
Then I'll pour it for you.

88
00:04:55,019 --> 00:04:56,139
That's even less necessary.

89
00:04:57,259 --> 00:04:59,019
You just recovered.

90
00:04:59,860 --> 00:05:02,220
I might infect you again.

91
00:05:02,899 --> 00:05:05,060
If we keep cross-infecting each other like this,

92
00:05:05,339 --> 00:05:07,300
it'll be even worse.

93
00:05:07,699 --> 00:05:08,300
Then...

94
00:05:09,060 --> 00:05:10,360
I'll go pour it for you.

95
00:05:10,699 --> 00:05:12,379
That's the way.

96
00:05:14,060 --> 00:05:15,100
Ms. Liu.

97
00:05:15,620 --> 00:05:17,220
Sorry to trouble you.

98
00:05:18,060 --> 00:05:19,259
You're welcome.

99
00:05:24,420 --> 00:05:25,819
Boss Li, you're something else.

100
00:05:26,459 --> 00:05:28,740
I just got over my illness and now you're sick.

101
00:05:30,060 --> 00:05:30,939
What's so strange about that?

102
00:05:31,779 --> 00:05:33,100
If you can be sick, why can't I?

103
00:05:33,980 --> 00:05:36,180
Ms. Liu already diagnosed me.

104
00:05:36,180 --> 00:05:37,740
A forehead full of cold sweat.

105
00:05:37,740 --> 00:05:39,379
Does Ms. Liu count?

106
00:05:39,500 --> 00:05:40,540
For a diagnosis,

107
00:05:40,819 --> 00:05:42,019
you need a professional, right?

108
00:05:42,019 --> 00:05:42,420
That's right.

109
00:05:42,420 --> 00:05:43,579
What do you mean?

110
00:05:44,060 --> 00:05:46,060
You don't trust Ms. Liu?

111
00:05:46,220 --> 00:05:46,660
Right.

112
00:05:47,100 --> 00:05:48,420
I don't trust myself either.

113
00:05:48,540 --> 00:05:49,540
Better get a professional.

114
00:05:49,660 --> 00:05:50,459
Summon Royal Physician Sun.

115
00:05:50,579 --> 00:05:51,339
Yes, sir.

116
00:05:51,540 --> 00:05:53,779
Yusheng, Zhu Zhu, summon the Royal Physician!

117
00:05:53,779 --> 00:05:55,259
Say no more. Come.

118
00:05:55,420 --> 00:05:56,579
Drink... drink some water.

119
00:06:02,220 --> 00:06:03,540
There's nothing wrong.

120
00:06:04,420 --> 00:06:06,339
Check a bit more carefully.

121
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:09,060
Don't be careless.

122
00:06:10,459 --> 00:06:11,699
There isn't anything.

123
00:06:12,819 --> 00:06:15,459
No murmurs.

124
00:06:16,540 --> 00:06:18,980
No rales.

125
00:06:20,579 --> 00:06:24,620
No abdominal bowel sounds.

126
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:26,759
Lungs,

127
00:06:28,259 --> 00:06:29,180
bronchi...

128
00:06:30,379 --> 00:06:32,339
How can there be nothing wrong?

129
00:06:33,379 --> 00:06:34,379
Listen to this.

130
00:06:37,180 --> 00:06:37,860
Sorry, Doctor.

131
00:06:37,860 --> 00:06:38,740
I'm sorry.

132
00:06:38,740 --> 00:06:40,220
What are you doing?

133
00:06:40,939 --> 00:06:41,740
Alright.

134
00:06:41,819 --> 00:06:43,180
Nothing major wrong.

135
00:06:43,939 --> 00:06:44,620
No, wait.

136
00:06:44,939 --> 00:06:46,459
You can't be so hasty.

137
00:06:46,699 --> 00:06:48,060
You didn't even check my pulse.

138
00:06:48,259 --> 00:06:48,980
No need.

139
00:06:49,139 --> 00:06:50,420
What's the point of checking the pulse?

140
00:06:50,699 --> 00:06:52,100
Just making trouble.

141
00:06:52,740 --> 00:06:53,100
No...

142
00:06:53,420 --> 00:06:55,699
Won't you leave some medical advice, Royal Physician?

143
00:06:58,019 --> 00:06:59,139
Keep the diet light.

144
00:06:59,180 --> 00:07:00,339
Drink plenty of hot water.

145
00:07:01,300 --> 00:07:02,819
What kind of advice is that?

146
00:07:02,819 --> 00:07:04,860
Who doesn't know to drink hot water?

147
00:07:05,579 --> 00:07:08,540
This patient really does need to drink plenty of hot water.

148
00:07:08,540 --> 00:07:09,819
Because the human body

149
00:07:09,819 --> 00:07:11,819
needs to flush out a lot of harmful substances.

150
00:07:11,819 --> 00:07:12,459
Right.

151
00:07:12,459 --> 00:07:14,939
But do you really count as a patient?

152
00:07:16,220 --> 00:07:17,339
Did you hear that?

153
00:07:18,500 --> 00:07:20,420
I need to flush out harmful substances.

154
00:07:20,660 --> 00:07:21,699
Lots of them.

155
00:07:21,939 --> 00:07:23,300
Hurry up and pour the water.

156
00:07:24,100 --> 00:07:24,860
Ms. Liu,

157
00:07:25,180 --> 00:07:26,339
please have a seat.

158
00:07:27,220 --> 00:07:27,939
Alright.

159
00:07:28,100 --> 00:07:29,259
Okay, I'll sit.

160
00:07:30,300 --> 00:07:30,740
Good.

161
00:07:37,079 --> 00:07:38,060
Take it easy.

162
00:07:39,899 --> 00:07:40,860
Slow down, it's hot.

163
00:07:40,860 --> 00:07:41,420
Slow down.

164
00:07:45,579 --> 00:07:46,259
Want some more?

165
00:07:47,339 --> 00:07:48,459
Tastes good.

166
00:07:49,339 --> 00:07:51,740
It'd be sweeter with some sugar.

167
00:07:52,300 --> 00:07:53,139
Grandpa Li.

168
00:07:53,339 --> 00:07:55,420
You don't look like you have a cold to me.

169
00:07:55,579 --> 00:07:57,339
Looks more like you drank too much hot water.

170
00:07:58,500 --> 00:07:58,939
Exactly.

171
00:07:58,939 --> 00:08:00,019
It's such a hot day.

172
00:08:00,019 --> 00:08:01,220
You're chugging all this hot water.

173
00:08:01,220 --> 00:08:02,459
And wrapped in such a thick quilt.

174
00:08:02,540 --> 00:08:03,579
How could you not sweat?

175
00:08:03,579 --> 00:08:04,259
Don't talk nonsense.

176
00:08:04,379 --> 00:08:05,180
What do you know?

177
00:08:05,420 --> 00:08:06,620
Ms. Liu even said...

178
00:08:07,259 --> 00:08:08,540
But Boss Li...

179
00:08:08,540 --> 00:08:10,819
You really don't look like you have a cold.

180
00:08:11,220 --> 00:08:12,939
Right. How about this...

181
00:08:13,180 --> 00:08:14,420
Stand up and take two steps.

182
00:08:14,459 --> 00:08:14,899
Right.

183
00:08:14,939 --> 00:08:16,100
You take two steps.

184
00:08:16,620 --> 00:08:18,540
Take two steps.

185
00:08:18,579 --> 00:08:24,339
Take two steps.

186
00:08:24,339 --> 00:08:25,180
Take two steps. Walk around.

187
00:08:25,180 --> 00:08:25,860
Can you?

188
00:08:26,060 --> 00:08:27,019
Try it.

189
00:08:27,139 --> 00:08:27,620
Well...

190
00:08:28,019 --> 00:08:28,660
Take two steps.

191
00:08:28,660 --> 00:08:29,620
Right, you take two steps.

192
00:08:29,620 --> 00:08:30,579
Here, take it slow.

193
00:08:30,939 --> 00:08:31,819
Take it slow.

194
00:08:32,179 --> 00:08:33,460
Here, take it slow.

195
00:08:33,460 --> 00:08:34,740
I'll hold you. Come on.

196
00:08:39,860 --> 00:08:40,820
Look.

197
00:08:41,259 --> 00:08:42,580
Look, once you stand up...

198
00:08:42,620 --> 00:08:44,059
You look perfectly fine.

199
00:08:44,100 --> 00:08:45,580
No, I mean, you clearly...

200
00:08:45,740 --> 00:08:46,580
...are much better.

201
00:08:46,580 --> 00:08:47,700
If you ask me...

202
00:08:48,179 --> 00:08:49,500
There's absolutely nothing wrong with him.

203
00:08:49,539 --> 00:08:50,740
You said it.

204
00:08:50,740 --> 00:08:53,100
I think Grandpa Li should rest and cool off.

205
00:08:53,100 --> 00:08:55,100
He'll be skipping to the cafeteria in no time.

206
00:08:57,419 --> 00:08:58,620
I stood up!

207
00:08:58,899 --> 00:09:00,379
That's amazing!

208
00:09:01,100 --> 00:09:02,179
Ms. Liu.

209
00:09:02,460 --> 00:09:04,139
You've cured my illness!

210
00:09:04,700 --> 00:09:05,860
You have a pair of magical hands!

211
00:09:05,860 --> 00:09:06,580
No...

212
00:09:06,860 --> 00:09:07,340
I...

213
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:09,100
I'm not that capable.

214
00:09:09,179 --> 00:09:11,980
Really, you look fine now.

215
00:09:11,980 --> 00:09:13,340
Well then, you rest.

216
00:09:13,379 --> 00:09:14,580
I'll be going back now.

217
00:09:14,580 --> 00:09:15,019
Wait...

218
00:09:15,179 --> 00:09:16,720
I'm heading back to the dorm too.

219
00:09:16,720 --> 00:09:17,559
Bye, Grandpa Li.

220
00:09:17,700 --> 00:09:19,299
Ms. Liu, about my flowers...

221
00:09:19,440 --> 00:09:20,740
I got them. Thank you.

222
00:09:21,159 --> 00:09:21,799
Flowers?

223
00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:24,159
What flowers?

224
00:09:58,840 --> 00:09:59,960
Old Li.

225
00:10:00,480 --> 00:10:01,960
Why are you standing there?

226
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:03,120
You scared me.

227
00:10:04,840 --> 00:10:06,600
In the middle of the night, out of nowhere...

228
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:07,960
...you let out a yelp.

229
00:10:08,120 --> 00:10:09,399
You're the one who scared me.

230
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:11,200
What's so scary about me?

231
00:10:11,399 --> 00:10:12,720
How are you not scary?

232
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:14,200
It's pitch black here.

233
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:16,120
You're standing there like a big stone monument.

234
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:17,879
Who wouldn't be scared seeing that at night?

235
00:10:17,879 --> 00:10:18,639
What stone monument?

236
00:10:19,080 --> 00:10:19,879
A stone sculpture.

237
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:21,080
Look at me.

238
00:10:21,440 --> 00:10:22,559
Don't I look like a...

239
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:24,600
...statue standing tall...

240
00:10:24,879 --> 00:10:25,519
...against the wind?

241
00:10:25,720 --> 00:10:27,120
Oh, give it a rest.

242
00:10:27,399 --> 00:10:29,000
Old Li, in the middle of the night...

243
00:10:29,039 --> 00:10:30,200
...why are you standing there?

244
00:10:31,759 --> 00:10:33,600
You're reflecting on your behavior...

245
00:10:33,720 --> 00:10:35,240
...from this afternoon, right?

246
00:10:36,519 --> 00:10:37,120
Not bad.

247
00:10:38,399 --> 00:10:39,440
I did reflect for a while.

248
00:10:40,919 --> 00:10:42,000
But after reflecting...

249
00:10:43,519 --> 00:10:44,320
...I got insomnia.

250
00:10:45,279 --> 00:10:46,480
Insomnia?

251
00:10:47,440 --> 00:10:49,480
You can try counting sheep.

252
00:10:49,480 --> 00:10:50,440
They say it works well.

253
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:50,960
I did.

254
00:10:51,360 --> 00:10:52,840
I counted I don't know how many sheep.

255
00:10:53,559 --> 00:10:54,480
The more I counted, the hungrier I got.

256
00:10:55,399 --> 00:10:56,519
I started craving hot pot mutton.

257
00:10:57,480 --> 00:10:58,360
Lamb skewers would work too.

258
00:10:58,720 --> 00:10:59,720
You want a midnight snack?

259
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:01,120
Then don't think about sheep.

260
00:11:01,360 --> 00:11:02,200
Think about something else.

261
00:11:02,399 --> 00:11:02,700
I did.

262
00:11:02,700 --> 00:11:03,519
Playing ping pong...

263
00:11:03,799 --> 00:11:04,559
...swimming and stuff.

264
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:05,960
I thought about those too.

265
00:11:07,080 --> 00:11:08,639
Just now, while you were grinding your teeth, snoring...

266
00:11:08,639 --> 00:11:10,440
...and smacking your lips...

267
00:11:11,159 --> 00:11:13,320
...I went through the breaststroke...

268
00:11:13,879 --> 00:11:15,080
...I learned in the army...

269
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:17,679
...freestyle...

270
00:11:18,679 --> 00:11:20,399
...even the doggy paddle...

271
00:11:21,039 --> 00:11:22,240
...I went through them all.

272
00:11:22,840 --> 00:11:23,519
It was no use.

273
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:24,600
You're talking nonsense.

274
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:25,519
Complete nonsense.

275
00:11:25,759 --> 00:11:26,879
I don't snore.

276
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:28,320
How do you know you don't snore?

277
00:11:28,879 --> 00:11:30,919
You've never shared a bed with anyone.

278
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:32,279
How would you know you don't snore?

279
00:11:33,279 --> 00:11:34,080
Anyway, I don't.

280
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:35,279
You snore quite a lot.

281
00:11:35,720 --> 00:11:37,440
And it comes in waves.

282
00:11:37,559 --> 00:11:38,200
You snore and snore...

283
00:11:39,960 --> 00:11:40,759
...then you stop breathing.

284
00:11:41,080 --> 00:11:41,879
I even have to check...

285
00:11:41,879 --> 00:11:43,159
...to see if you're breathing.

286
00:11:43,279 --> 00:11:44,440
Scared you might die.

287
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:48,120
That's sleep apnea syndrome.

288
00:11:49,399 --> 00:11:50,360
What is it?

289
00:11:50,840 --> 00:11:53,399
It's sleep apnea syndrome.

290
00:11:53,720 --> 00:11:54,559
You have this condition.

291
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:56,879
It seems when people get old...

292
00:11:57,039 --> 00:11:58,919
...having someone nearby is really important.

293
00:11:59,360 --> 00:12:00,200
Thank you, Old Li.

294
00:12:00,419 --> 00:12:01,519
What's there to thank?

295
00:12:02,600 --> 00:12:04,440
Just my luck to share a room with you.

296
00:12:04,720 --> 00:12:05,720
Just have to put up with it.

297
00:12:21,139 --> 00:12:22,159
Hello, Ms. Liu.

298
00:12:22,179 --> 00:12:23,100
Morning, Ms. Liu.

299
00:12:23,100 --> 00:12:24,019
You're up so early.

300
00:12:24,299 --> 00:12:25,419
What early?

301
00:12:25,659 --> 00:12:27,059
We didn't sleep at all.

302
00:12:28,779 --> 00:12:29,820
Why?

303
00:12:30,019 --> 00:12:30,460
It's all because...

304
00:12:30,460 --> 00:12:32,539
...Little Fan had insomnia last night.

305
00:12:32,539 --> 00:12:33,820
I took care of him all night.

306
00:12:34,019 --> 00:12:36,299
What? Aren't you twisting the truth?

307
00:12:36,379 --> 00:12:37,700
Clearly you had insomnia.

308
00:12:37,700 --> 00:12:39,259
I chatted with you all night, okay?

309
00:12:39,259 --> 00:12:40,580
Clearly you had insomnia.

310
00:12:40,580 --> 00:12:41,340
I took care of him all night.

311
00:12:41,340 --> 00:12:42,379
Alright.

312
00:12:42,379 --> 00:12:44,659
Is this worth arguing about?

313
00:12:46,139 --> 00:12:47,899
You don't understand nursing; you might make it worse.

314
00:12:48,059 --> 00:12:49,779
Nursing is a job for us women.

315
00:12:49,779 --> 00:12:50,460
In a bit...

316
00:12:50,460 --> 00:12:51,820
...I'll go over and check on you guys.

317
00:12:52,379 --> 00:12:52,899
By the way...

318
00:12:54,179 --> 00:12:55,700
...who was the one with insomnia?

319
00:12:56,299 --> 00:12:58,379
I... I had insomnia.

320
00:12:58,379 --> 00:12:59,340
You?

321
00:13:03,980 --> 00:13:06,019
You fight me for food at meals

322
00:13:06,299 --> 00:13:08,500
You fight me for water in the shower

323
00:13:09,299 --> 00:13:12,019
You fight me for the remote when watching TV

324
00:13:12,860 --> 00:13:14,100
Now it's even better

325
00:13:15,379 --> 00:13:17,580
You're even competing with me to be sick

326
00:13:18,299 --> 00:13:20,019
You get jealous of everything you see

327
00:13:20,019 --> 00:13:21,500
What is wrong with you?

328
00:13:21,820 --> 00:13:23,340
Who's competing with you?

329
00:13:23,620 --> 00:13:25,059
Yesterday you copied me having a fever

330
00:13:25,220 --> 00:13:26,899
Chugging hot water like crazy

331
00:13:26,899 --> 00:13:27,539
Who was that?

332
00:13:28,299 --> 00:13:29,179
Enough

333
00:13:29,580 --> 00:13:30,860
Didn't we agree?

334
00:13:31,059 --> 00:13:33,059
We wouldn't expose each other's faults anymore

335
00:13:33,259 --> 00:13:34,740
The one drinking hot water yesterday...

336
00:13:36,059 --> 00:13:37,980
That was just an isolated incident

337
00:13:41,139 --> 00:13:42,740
Don't you... with a sick person like me...

338
00:13:42,740 --> 00:13:44,860
...keep pestering me unreasonably, okay?

339
00:13:45,100 --> 00:13:48,100
I didn't sleep a wink all last night

340
00:13:48,179 --> 00:13:50,019
Can't you cut me some slack?

341
00:13:50,019 --> 00:13:50,820
Fine

342
00:13:50,820 --> 00:13:52,019
I'll let you have your way

343
00:13:53,179 --> 00:13:54,580
But who's going to cut me some slack?

344
00:13:54,620 --> 00:13:56,700
I also didn't sleep a wink all night

345
00:13:57,139 --> 00:13:58,220
Professor Fan

346
00:13:58,940 --> 00:13:59,899
I know

347
00:14:00,460 --> 00:14:02,220
To keep me company...

348
00:14:02,779 --> 00:14:04,860
You also didn't sleep a wink all night

349
00:14:05,899 --> 00:14:08,580
This fully shows how learned you are...

350
00:14:08,980 --> 00:14:10,620
And highly respected

351
00:14:11,299 --> 00:14:13,340
Dedicating your heart and talent...

352
00:14:13,620 --> 00:14:15,779
...to us, the older generation

353
00:14:17,019 --> 00:14:20,220
You are the one I admire and respect most...

354
00:14:20,539 --> 00:14:21,860
The most lovable person

355
00:14:22,259 --> 00:14:23,500
What I like is...

356
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:25,059
Stop right there

357
00:14:26,299 --> 00:14:27,700
It's the exact same words...

358
00:14:28,220 --> 00:14:29,740
But when you say them...

359
00:14:30,019 --> 00:14:31,539
Why does it sound so awkward?

360
00:14:31,740 --> 00:14:33,100
What's awkward about it?

361
00:14:33,500 --> 00:14:34,460
So...

362
00:14:35,179 --> 00:14:37,379
I hope you keep up this style

363
00:14:37,620 --> 00:14:39,899
And go to sleep like a good boy

364
00:14:40,059 --> 00:14:41,820
So that Ms. Liu...

365
00:14:41,899 --> 00:14:45,379
Can treat me with peace of mind

366
00:14:45,460 --> 00:14:47,860
I knew you were up to no good when you praised me

367
00:14:48,179 --> 00:14:49,980
I'm telling you, this time I'm just...

368
00:14:50,100 --> 00:14:50,860
Not giving in

369
00:14:51,220 --> 00:14:53,139
How can you be like this?

370
00:14:53,139 --> 00:14:54,379
Why can't I?

371
00:14:54,379 --> 00:14:55,480
The business of insomnia...

372
00:14:55,480 --> 00:14:57,019
Do you have a monopoly on it?

373
00:14:57,139 --> 00:14:58,740
So only you are allowed...

374
00:14:58,940 --> 00:15:00,100
To play at having insomnia?

375
00:15:00,179 --> 00:15:01,820
And I can't be unable to sleep?

376
00:15:01,860 --> 00:15:03,580
People fight over titles and honors...

377
00:15:03,799 --> 00:15:05,779
But fighting to get sick?

378
00:15:06,259 --> 00:15:07,320
Why should this doctor...

379
00:15:07,320 --> 00:15:08,700
Be hogged by you alone?

380
00:15:09,019 --> 00:15:09,580
You...

381
00:15:10,019 --> 00:15:10,500
No...

382
00:15:11,139 --> 00:15:11,879
How can you...

383
00:15:11,879 --> 00:15:13,299
Be so unreasonable?

384
00:15:13,980 --> 00:15:14,620
With you making such a fuss...

385
00:15:14,620 --> 00:15:15,860
My head hurts even more

386
00:15:16,220 --> 00:15:18,059
Although I have a history of insomnia...

387
00:15:18,059 --> 00:15:19,899
It's not like I can have insomnia on command

388
00:15:20,100 --> 00:15:21,700
This once-in-a-lifetime chance for me...

389
00:15:21,700 --> 00:15:22,940
And you're fighting me for it?

390
00:15:24,539 --> 00:15:25,539
How about this...

391
00:15:25,980 --> 00:15:27,179
Ms. Liu is one person

392
00:15:27,220 --> 00:15:28,379
And there are two of us

393
00:15:28,500 --> 00:15:29,980
Which patient she takes care of...

394
00:15:30,059 --> 00:15:31,419
Depends on who is sicker

395
00:15:32,779 --> 00:15:34,299
From now on, I declare...

396
00:15:34,659 --> 00:15:35,620
I officially have insomnia

397
00:15:35,700 --> 00:15:36,580
Who's afraid of whom?

398
00:15:36,940 --> 00:15:37,980
From now on...

399
00:15:38,539 --> 00:15:39,379
Officially insomnia

400
00:15:39,980 --> 00:15:40,620
Wait, that's not right

401
00:15:41,379 --> 00:15:43,100
I started having insomnia yesterday

402
00:15:44,980 --> 00:15:46,100
Boss Li, Professor Fan

403
00:15:46,379 --> 00:15:47,740
Which one of you actually has insomnia?

404
00:15:47,740 --> 00:15:48,139
Me

405
00:15:48,139 --> 00:15:49,419
I have insomnia

406
00:15:52,220 --> 00:15:54,019
I can't sleep night after night.

407
00:15:54,460 --> 00:15:56,620
I can't close my eyes all night long.

408
00:15:58,299 --> 00:15:58,740
You...

409
00:15:58,980 --> 00:15:59,580
Look.

410
00:16:00,179 --> 00:16:01,419
Whenever I scroll through TikTok,

411
00:16:01,740 --> 00:16:02,379
I just...

412
00:16:02,740 --> 00:16:03,899
get incredibly excited.

413
00:16:04,220 --> 00:16:05,899
I toss and turn in bed like a pancake.

414
00:16:06,299 --> 00:16:09,379
Once I lie down, if I get up to use the bathroom,

415
00:16:09,460 --> 00:16:10,940
I just want to grab a book

416
00:16:11,059 --> 00:16:12,779
and sit on the toilet all night.

417
00:16:12,840 --> 00:16:14,440
I can't sleep at night.

418
00:16:14,440 --> 00:16:15,960
I have no energy during the day.

419
00:16:16,159 --> 00:16:19,399
I've lost my sleep.

420
00:16:19,440 --> 00:16:21,519
I treat the night like the day.

421
00:16:21,759 --> 00:16:24,519
And the day like the night... and like the day too.

422
00:16:24,580 --> 00:16:25,460
Ms. Liu,

423
00:16:26,100 --> 00:16:27,379
look at my eyes.

424
00:16:27,620 --> 00:16:29,320
I look exactly like a panda.

425
00:16:29,559 --> 00:16:31,440
These two big dark circles.

426
00:16:31,659 --> 00:16:32,360
Ms. Liu,

427
00:16:33,039 --> 00:16:34,879
look at my eyes.

428
00:16:34,940 --> 00:16:35,840
Whatever a goldfish looks like,

429
00:16:35,840 --> 00:16:37,000
that's what I look like.

430
00:16:37,279 --> 00:16:38,200
Staring blankly,

431
00:16:38,440 --> 00:16:39,120
without blinking.

432
00:16:40,639 --> 00:16:42,159
It seems you two old brothers

433
00:16:42,360 --> 00:16:43,419
are quite ill.

434
00:16:43,539 --> 00:16:44,419
Who's brothers with him?

435
00:16:44,460 --> 00:16:45,740
We have our own separate illnesses.

436
00:16:45,879 --> 00:16:46,620
But I...

437
00:16:47,139 --> 00:16:48,139
I'm just one person.

438
00:16:48,220 --> 00:16:50,100
I can't take care of both of you.

439
00:16:50,100 --> 00:16:51,100
Oh my goodness.

440
00:16:51,419 --> 00:16:53,500
Boss Li, Professor Fan.

441
00:16:53,539 --> 00:16:54,580
When I woke up this morning,

442
00:16:54,659 --> 00:16:56,139
I heard you two were sick.

443
00:16:56,620 --> 00:16:59,700
Oh, I was so worried.

444
00:17:00,059 --> 00:17:01,299
I rolled over and fell right back asleep.

445
00:17:01,299 --> 00:17:02,899
Look how that delayed things.

446
00:17:03,179 --> 00:17:04,140
Ms. Liu,

447
00:17:04,299 --> 00:17:06,220
if you need any help, just give a cough.

448
00:17:06,660 --> 00:17:08,819
You're just in time.

449
00:17:09,839 --> 00:17:10,660
What's wrong?

450
00:17:12,500 --> 00:17:13,299
Ms. Liu,

451
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:16,420
this minor ailment of mine

452
00:17:17,099 --> 00:17:18,779
is causing you so much trouble.

453
00:17:20,420 --> 00:17:22,099
I'm really embarrassed.

454
00:17:23,180 --> 00:17:23,940
Boss Li,

455
00:17:24,259 --> 00:17:25,700
don't say that.

456
00:17:26,180 --> 00:17:27,819
You hold a high position,

457
00:17:27,940 --> 00:17:29,500
dominating the business world,

458
00:17:29,740 --> 00:17:31,940
commanding thousands of troops,

459
00:17:32,059 --> 00:17:34,099
creating immense wealth.

460
00:17:34,279 --> 00:17:36,799
For the great rejuvenation of the Chinese nation,

461
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:39,599
you've made such a huge contribution.

462
00:17:39,960 --> 00:17:42,839
I've always admired you the most,

463
00:17:44,519 --> 00:17:46,400
such an influential figure.

464
00:17:46,960 --> 00:17:47,759
Really.

465
00:17:48,799 --> 00:17:50,079
Ms. Liu, do you really

466
00:17:50,559 --> 00:17:52,039
have such an opinion of me?

467
00:17:55,480 --> 00:17:58,559
I actually never felt it before.

468
00:18:01,200 --> 00:18:02,359
I was too careless.

469
00:18:03,279 --> 00:18:04,359
Too confused.

470
00:18:05,339 --> 00:18:06,599
Too slow-witted.

471
00:18:08,440 --> 00:18:09,839
But it doesn't matter.

472
00:18:11,119 --> 00:18:12,960
We can start from now.

473
00:18:12,960 --> 00:18:14,440
Time's up.

474
00:18:15,240 --> 00:18:15,920
We agreed,

475
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:16,960
switch every ten minutes.

476
00:18:17,079 --> 00:18:17,680
Time is up.

477
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:18,680
Time to switch.

478
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:19,359
Why should I?

479
00:18:19,359 --> 00:18:20,119
On what grounds?

480
00:18:20,119 --> 00:18:21,640
It's barely been five minutes.

481
00:18:21,640 --> 00:18:22,799
Why switch now?

482
00:18:23,359 --> 00:18:24,279
If you want to switch,

483
00:18:24,279 --> 00:18:26,200
you have to wait for me to finish the story. Listen.

484
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:30,079
Right at this critical moment,

485
00:18:30,559 --> 00:18:32,240
one could hear from inside the coffin...

486
00:18:37,799 --> 00:18:38,920
Someone is crying.

487
00:18:40,119 --> 00:18:41,799
Look at that coffin lid again.

488
00:18:46,680 --> 00:18:47,720
Alright.

489
00:18:47,799 --> 00:18:48,920
Time's up. Switch.

490
00:18:49,480 --> 00:18:50,319
Old Fan.

491
00:18:51,400 --> 00:18:53,759
I think you should just hurry up and sleep.

492
00:18:54,660 --> 00:18:57,039
Sister Cai is telling such a wonderful story.

493
00:18:57,039 --> 00:18:59,119
Isn't it just to coax you to sleep?

494
00:18:59,519 --> 00:19:00,599
Once you fall asleep,

495
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:02,720
Sister Cai will naturally stop telling it.

496
00:19:03,079 --> 00:19:04,039
I can't sleep.

497
00:19:04,480 --> 00:19:05,400
If I sleep,

498
00:19:05,519 --> 00:19:06,039
she...

499
00:19:06,519 --> 00:19:07,200
...they...

500
00:19:07,920 --> 00:19:08,880
won't they all leave?

501
00:19:10,119 --> 00:19:11,559
You just can't bear for me to leave, right?

502
00:19:12,720 --> 00:19:13,799
I knew it.

503
00:19:13,920 --> 00:19:15,720
My story is so good.

504
00:19:15,759 --> 00:19:18,640
Suspense, horror, mystery.

505
00:19:18,680 --> 00:19:20,119
This story of mine,

506
00:19:20,200 --> 00:19:23,079
"Red Braised Pork in the Morgue" is just captivating.

507
00:19:23,079 --> 00:19:23,680
Right?

508
00:19:23,759 --> 00:19:25,279
Listen to one part, you want two.

509
00:19:25,279 --> 00:19:27,200
The more scared you are, the more you want to listen.

510
00:19:27,240 --> 00:19:28,640
You don't want to sleep now, do you?

511
00:19:28,720 --> 00:19:30,000
I'll continue telling you.

512
00:19:30,559 --> 00:19:32,079
This coffin...

513
00:19:32,440 --> 00:19:33,400
Okay.

514
00:19:33,480 --> 00:19:34,200
I beg you.

515
00:19:34,200 --> 00:19:35,519
I beg you, Sister.

516
00:19:35,519 --> 00:19:36,160
Sister.

517
00:19:36,599 --> 00:19:37,839
Even if I...

518
00:19:38,039 --> 00:19:38,880
fall asleep,

519
00:19:39,059 --> 00:19:40,400
I'd have fainted from your scare.

520
00:19:40,619 --> 00:19:42,759
I'd have nightmares even in a coma.

521
00:19:43,440 --> 00:19:44,279
Tell it to Old Li.

522
00:19:44,720 --> 00:19:45,640
Tell it to Old Li.

523
00:19:46,039 --> 00:19:46,799
That works too.

524
00:19:48,599 --> 00:19:50,279
To know what happens next,

525
00:19:50,559 --> 00:19:52,640
please listen to the afternoon chapter.

526
00:19:53,380 --> 00:19:54,000
Ms. Liu.

527
00:19:54,420 --> 00:19:54,920
Switch.

528
00:19:55,359 --> 00:19:55,880
Okay.

529
00:20:01,599 --> 00:20:02,559
Professor Fan.

530
00:20:04,420 --> 00:20:06,200
Do you feel any better?

531
00:20:06,440 --> 00:20:07,359
As soon as you came over,

532
00:20:08,039 --> 00:20:09,079
I felt much better.

533
00:20:10,119 --> 00:20:10,799
Boss Li.

534
00:20:11,200 --> 00:20:13,960
You've heard those old stories eight hundred times.

535
00:20:13,960 --> 00:20:15,160
You don't care to listen anymore, right?

536
00:20:15,279 --> 00:20:17,000
Let's try something original.

537
00:20:17,079 --> 00:20:19,279
I'll tell you one I just finished reading.

538
00:20:19,880 --> 00:20:21,000
Magical,

539
00:20:21,079 --> 00:20:22,240
horror,

540
00:20:22,680 --> 00:20:24,680
mystery novel.

541
00:20:24,759 --> 00:20:26,440
"The Green Right Hand".

542
00:20:27,799 --> 00:20:28,720
Green...

543
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:29,920
and a right hand?

544
00:20:30,359 --> 00:20:32,319
If you want a left hand, I have that too.

545
00:20:32,400 --> 00:20:33,599
No need.

546
00:20:34,200 --> 00:20:37,200
Boss Li, don't be polite with me.

547
00:20:37,319 --> 00:20:38,880
Ms. Liu told me,

548
00:20:39,119 --> 00:20:41,400
you really love listening to stories.

549
00:20:41,880 --> 00:20:43,319
And not only do you listen,

550
00:20:43,319 --> 00:20:44,640
you also love telling them.

551
00:20:44,720 --> 00:20:46,000
This is how you tell it:

552
00:20:46,279 --> 00:20:47,960
Once upon a time there was a mountain.

553
00:20:48,240 --> 00:20:49,880
In the mountain there was a temple.

554
00:20:50,160 --> 00:20:52,039
In the temple there was a little ghost.

555
00:20:53,160 --> 00:20:54,359
It went into a coffin.

556
00:20:55,960 --> 00:20:57,480
*Creak creak*

557
00:20:57,640 --> 00:20:59,440
Did I mix up the stories?

558
00:20:59,519 --> 00:21:01,559
What did I do to deserve this?

559
00:21:01,559 --> 00:21:02,279
Boss Li.

560
00:21:02,920 --> 00:21:05,000
I advise you to hurry up and sleep.

561
00:21:05,640 --> 00:21:07,759
Sister Cai is telling you such a wonderful story.

562
00:21:07,880 --> 00:21:08,559
Isn't it just

563
00:21:08,920 --> 00:21:10,039
to make you sleep?

564
00:21:10,400 --> 00:21:11,400
As long as you fall asleep,

565
00:21:11,480 --> 00:21:12,559
Sister Cai will stop.

566
00:21:12,839 --> 00:21:13,799
Sister Cai stops,

567
00:21:14,119 --> 00:21:15,480
and Ms. Liu stays with you permanently?

568
00:21:15,880 --> 00:21:16,640
Dream on.

569
00:21:16,680 --> 00:21:17,839
Even if I'm sleepy,

570
00:21:19,079 --> 00:21:20,039
I won't sleep.

571
00:21:20,680 --> 00:21:21,119
You...

572
00:21:21,359 --> 00:21:21,759
No...

573
00:21:21,839 --> 00:21:22,319
You...

574
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:27,119
Ms. Liu.

575
00:21:27,720 --> 00:21:30,880
Is it that I don't tell stories well?

576
00:21:33,119 --> 00:21:33,680
Just...

577
